wikipedia_page.main: Sir Charles Henry Wilson (13 January 1859 – 30 December 1930) was a British Conservative Party politician. He was the Member of Parliament (MP) for Leeds Central, 26 July 1923 – 30 May 1929.Wilson was a councillor and alderman on Leeds City Council from 1890 to 1928, and council leader for a period, and also an accountant, Justice of the Peace and Freeman of the City.
